EC2 + RDS + IAM + CloudWatch Monitoring (AWS Project)

📌 Project Overview

This project demonstrates building a simple web application hosted on EC2, connected to an RDS MySQL database, secured using IAM roles, and monitored using CloudWatch.

🎯 Objectives
Connect EC2 instance to RDS database
Implement secure access using IAM roles
Monitor system metrics using CloudWatch
Perform real-world troubleshooting scenarios
🏗️ Architecture
EC2 instance hosting a web application
RDS MySQL database for backend storage
IAM Role attached to EC2 for secure access
CloudWatch for monitoring metrics and logs
🛠️ Implementation Steps
🔹 1. Launch EC2 Instance
Amazon Linux 2
Enabled:
SSH (22)
HTTP (80)
🔹 2. Create RDS Database
Engine: MySQL
Database name: testdb
Enabled public access (for testing)
🔹 3. Configure Security Groups
Allowed EC2 → RDS communication on port 3306
🔹 4. Connect EC2 to RDS

Installed MySQL client:

sudo yum install mysql -y

Connected using:

mysql -h <RDS-ENDPOINT> -u admin -p
🔹 5. Create Database & Table
CREATE DATABASE testdb;
USE testdb;

CREATE TABLE users (
  id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
  name VARCHAR(50)
);

INSERT INTO users (name) VALUES ('Siddhi');
🔹 6. Create Web Application

Installed PHP:

sudo yum install php php-mysqlnd -y

Created index.php to fetch data from RDS.

🔹 7. Configure IAM Role
Created IAM role for EC2
Attached CloudWatch access policy
Enabled secure access without credentials
🔹 8. Setup CloudWatch Monitoring

Installed CloudWatch Agent:

sudo yum install amazon-cloudwatch-agent -y

Configured manually using JSON file and started agent.

🧪 Challenges Faced & Solutions
❌ MySQL Installation Failed (GPG Error)

Cause: Outdated repository GPG key

Fix: Updated GPG key and cleaned yum cache

❌ Unable to Connect to RDS

Cause: Security group not allowing port 3306

Fix: Allowed EC2 security group in RDS inbound rules

❌ CloudWatch Agent Wizard Failed

Cause: Missing old configuration file

Fix: Created configuration manually and started agent via CLI

❌ Incorrect MySQL Command Syntax

Cause: Used placeholder <RDS-ENDPOINT>

Fix: Replaced with actual endpoint

